The chamber fell still. [] has seen his sister wear many masks in court, but not one filled with grief, betrayal and contest.  It did not suit her. Or perhaps, it suited her too well. 
The throne stood untouched, but not unclaimed. 
In the hollow left by the Mudhaliyar’s mourning, something was stirring —not mourning, but momentum 
In Vasudev’s absence, a faction in his name is being formed, to contest. A faction in House Mudhaliyar is shattering of oaths, something the house has never seen. A fracture in this House, would be a fracture of allegiances in the South.
